\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Well - on Windsor Bridge, yes, in the neighbourhood - in the comm
unity - and this Yes, used to go to the ragged school every week. Sundays. And it was a well known family used to - still going - well known family - MacDougalls. The - no not - the paint people, they're - they're one of the family. And a matter of fact o
ne of the grand - grandsons still comes to our house at the moment - he does come - he comes after - he's a friend of both my daughters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Was this an actual school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
It was - it wasn't a day school, it was just a Sunday school. But there used to b
e activities all week going on. Oh - weekly adventure was to go to the penny - pictures which was slides - slide pictures - that was looked forward to every week. This - at the ragged school, yes. And we used to have a temperance society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Tell me about the temperance society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 We had a temperance society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 What happened there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
Used to have a - I was a member - used to have Bible - Bible classes and - recreation games and we used to do all sorts of activities - used to put plays on - all 
scholars and then we had this - the little folks. There was a - a - one society there called the little folks and they had - all activities for children. And people put a lot of work in. The MacDougall family - they put a lot of work in. and a lot of peop
l
e put work in - teachers and young men - voluntary - was one of the finest brass bands. World famous brass band. The old Institute band, it was called then it was changed from ragged school it was called - later on it was called Windsor Institute and we h
ad a famous band.
