ou - you had to go all - all the way to - Manchester to a place called Fancy Street near the Salvation Army. Of course you had to walk it and you were interviewed there with this form and then you got a ticket. And on the day in - when - it was supposed -
 you were supposed to go away you all used to meet at the school. You went to town - Manchester. And then you all marched - I remember - with banners - Wood Street Mission, Poor }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2379883\charrsid7472631 Children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631  Camp and you marched to Central Station or - yes, I think it was Cen
tral Station or Victoria Station. And we used to go away for a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 How often did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Every year. Yes. If was lucky enough to get -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Oh did we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Where did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Birkdale. Yes. But it was - it was -
 it was another prison when you got there - it was another prison. Because it was surrounded by - they like - what we call them today - nisson huts. It was - we had tents - so many boys to a tent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Was it just boys went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Boys. And girls went. Yes
, I think girls went. I'm not sure now but I think girls went as well. No, I don't know - I couldn't be sure about that. But it was surrounded by a wall. It was right on the seashore but you couldn't see the sea of course - nobody could see the sea becaus
e it's so far away. But - it was surrounded by a wall on one side - a sea wall on one side and the railway on the other - the rail, and there you was confined for the full week you was there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 What did you do while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 We just played 
amongst ourselves and one day in the week we was taken out and taken to - a walk - I remember going round the - the lake - as a boy and seeing a crab in the water and putting me hand in to drag it out. But it was too quick for me - it nipped me in the pal
m of the hand, it - that was a highlight of that week that occasion anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did you enjoy the holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
Yes, it was something of a - of a change, but - I wasn't a person that could be confined. I wanted - I was a - I was a loner. I believe myself 
in those days I was a loner. I found great enjoyment in me own company. I wasn't selfish or anything like that, but I found great - because I could do things when I was on me own that I wouldn't attempt with anybody ever come - they'd be more or less the 
fly in the ointment, I wouldn't - I could go swimming in canals, I could go climbing bridges, I could do anything - 'cos I was of that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2379883\charrsid7472631 temperament}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631  and I used to revel in being on me own and doing things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did your mother attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Me mother used to go to the ragged school up -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 No, not regularly, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
You wouldn't know if your father took an interest in politics because he was away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 No, me father took an interest in nothing. Politics - I don't
 believe he even knew what politics was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
Me mother knew what politics was but she didn't take much interest in - only in later life. But me father didn't - he - he was oblivious of - of his surroundings me father. He just lived for the moment I believe. He was that type of fellow - yes..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
Was your mother in any savings clubs at all - boot clubs, sick clubs, funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
No, there - there - there's no sick clubs. No. If you had a doctor in those days - he's a - he's a 
little old family doctor in those days, I can remember one in particular and he - if mother - like a member of the family was ill or if you had people sick he came irrespective of what the weather was liked - he was a member of the family and he didn't as
k for his money and - he used to have what they called a doctor's man. Like a club collector today and he came round collecting - only paid sixpence - whatever you could afford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did your mum join an insurance club - a death club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Yes, of course i
n those days - when a child was born the clubman'd call straight away and if you had a death - if you had a club and somebody died and the club was for threepence - he - he'd - he'd get his - threepence back by making you, well not making you but - what w
ould you call it - he'd - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2379883\charrsid7472631 psychoanalyse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
 you until you - you put the threepence back in something else but all children when they was born was insured straight away - at the nominal fee of a penny a week. I've still got some to this day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Was there anyone you felt particularly close to as a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
No - I liked pals. Some pals I - I - I liked better than others but as I say I was - I - I was more or less a loner. As I got older I went more along because I found that I could do things that - having n
o parental control - I had got into a way of life than I - I was allowed to - to run about as I wanted but other children - of my own age couldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Who did you play with then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Well I used to play with the - neighbours children yes, and then -
 and then I used to - when they was all had to go to bed and - different things, I used to be off on me own and - on weekends I used to go on me own - I used to take a - piece of wrapper a couple of eggs, three or four rounds of bread and go and get up in
 Bluebell Woods or up at - up Thirteen Arches which is well known, and spend all the weekend there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Sleep out there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Sleep out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 When you were playing did you play in the house, garden, street or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Well, played in the street, yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Do you remember the games you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
But - in those days - which is I - I found a - a great difference in the children of today. The children of today as I see them they spend all their time round their own neighbourhood, they play footba
ll in the street. They don't attend the parks like they used to do. Now if I wasn't in the park ; when I left school of an evening if I wasn't in the park playing football or on the swings, what they call the - not the ordinary swings, the gymnastic swing
s, I was up the canal swimming. That was of course in a - in good weather. And - I never spent no time hardly in the neighbourhood. I was never under me mother's feet all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 So you were allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Oh yes. I used 
to wash meself in the canal. Of course - swimming in the canal. But - I never was hanging round the neighbourhood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did you have any hobbies at all when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 I remember the first wireless first came in. I - begged, borrowed or - stol
e as you could say, bits and pieces of things and tried to make a crystal set. I remember - getting -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 What year would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
Oh - it must be about in 1908 or something like that. I remember buying a - a - oh, I didn't buy them, I went to the m
arket and - where they used to have - cardboard rolls used to put tape on - I got two off a chap there, one was bigger than the other so one could go inside the other then I got the - covered wire and bared it in a certain places and that was the - the tu
ner or something and I bought a crystal - a crystal I think was ninepence, I'm not sure, and tried to build a tel - a set.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did you ever go to theatres or pictures while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Yes. I used to go to the theatre but I never paid. 
I always - I always found ways and means of getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2379883\charrsid7472631 in. Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
 - in one place my mother was working at one place that was a theatre. Price of Wales' theatre in Liverpool Street. Of course I had open sesame there, I could go there any time I wanted. But when sh
e left there and - and it became a picture house - it was a theatre when I'm }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1277943\charrsid7472631 telling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631  about but it became picture house. And as I knew every nook and cranny of that place - there was ways and means of getting in there even the man - the man that bought it d
idn't know anything about, but I did. And of course I used to go in when I wanted. And take friends in. And - other places - I found other theatres - the Hippodrome - the famous Hippodrome - I found a way of getting in there. So I suppose - I - I showed a
 little bit of enterprise in that respect and got in there for nothing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did anybody ever give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 No. No. The only - the only pocket money I ever got was what I earned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 This was while you ware a child at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 How did you earn it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 I used to go - as soon -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 Did you have a part time job while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
No, it - there was no such - no part time jobs like there is now. I used to come home from school at dinner time, when we had - when I went to the industrial school I'm talking about and I used to go on the tip. The tip at New Park -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 This was the rubbish heap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
I was - oh, about seven or eight acres of ground there and maybe more and they was filling it in. And I used t
o go there and pick iron. And - a friend of mine - his - his father was the - rag and bone people and I used to go and pick about four or five pound of iron and I'd take it home and - after }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1277943\charrsid7472631 school and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631  I used to take it to Mr Lights and weigh it in, and I g
ot fourpence maybe. That's how I got my money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8484072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1133603 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4400345\charrsid7472631 
Well me first full time job - I made an application got to the - tramways and of course you had to wait those days for - get in. and I got recommended by certain p
eople for the job but while I was waiting for it I went to the gas works. A place called Conlin Steeles and you started at six in the morning 'til six at night and I got nine shilling.
